{{Quote|It is a mystery why one would call Gorc and Pic twins. Even though one is a miniature version of the other, they look nothing alike. They also don't battle alike. Pic is the energy and Gorc, the counter. They are the clashing balance of opposites: one, the voice; the other, the body. This combination is deadly.|Qu Rahn as a Force ghost, to Kyle Katarn|audio=QuRahn-GorcPic.flac|<ref name="JK2">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]''</ref>}}
'''Brothers of the Sith''' was the title used by the so-called "twins" [[Picaroon C. Boodle]] and [[Gorc]], while serving as two of [[Jerec (Inquisitor)|Jerec's]] [[Seven Dark Jedi|Seven]] [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]]. They were sometimes also called '''the Twins'''.

Pic and Gorc were not siblings, and neither were they [[Sith/Legends|Sith]]. They were, in fact, the result of an experiment in [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemy]] carried out by [[Cronal]] under orders from [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Cronal mutated a [[Kowakian monkey-lizard/Legends|Kowakian monkey-lizard]] and a [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] by exchanging genes between them, artifically making them genetic "brothers". As a result of the mutation, the two [[Sithspawn/Legends|Sithspawn]] shared a Force life-bond that resulted in the ability of each to feel the others' location, emotional state, and senses, including even pain.<ref name="saga5">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050609a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 5: Two Peas in a Pod}}</ref>

When seen together, the Twins seemed like a comical pair, owing to their difference in intelligence, talkativeness, size, height, strength and mass. In practice this meant that they covered a wide range of abilities, complementing each other. Between the two, the more intelligent Pic had the role of the "big brother," caring also for [[Boc Aseca|Boc]].<ref name="saga5" />

The pair went on to serve [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitor]] Jerec as two of his [[Seven Dark Jedi]] and participated in the execution of [[Qu Rahn/Legends|Qu Rahn's]] team and the deactivation of [[8t88/Legends|8t88]]. When Jerec and his Dark Jedi faced [[Kyle Katarn]], Gorc was killed and the [[Force-bond/Legends|bond]] that Pic shared with his "brother" caused the living twin to feel as if half of him had died. Pic accordingly fell into a mad frenzy until he joined his other half in death.<ref name="Rebel Agent">''[[Dark Forces: Rebel Agent]]''</ref>

==Powers and abilities==
Individually, Pic's speed and cunning alongside Gorc's raw power went hand-in-hand during battles. The two always worked and battled as a team, covering all angles and weaknesses making their combination a deadly one.<ref name="saga5" /> Pic often rendered himself invisible while Gorc often [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force Grip|choked]] his opponents telekinetically, immobilizing them. As Rahn described, "''Pic is the energy and Gorc the counter''."<ref name="JK2" />

The Twins shared awareness and some [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathy]]; each individual knew the other's location, senses and emotional state, and when they were in close proximity, they individually became more [[Force power/Legends|powerful]]. The side-effect was that they also shared pain, injuries, and corruption by the dark side. When Gorc was killed, the surviving part of the pair felt like losing his half life.<ref name="saga5" />

==Behind the scenes==
In ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]'', the level in which the player must face Gorc and Pic (Level number 11) is titled "Brothers of the Sith," and [[Qu Rahn/Legends|Qu Rahn]] describes the two as twins. Details of their relationship are expanded on by [[Wizards of the Coast]].

